===Etymology===
From Afrikaans ''[[#Afrikaans|springbok]]'', from Dutch ''[[springen]]'' ‘to spring’ + ''[[bok]]'' ‘goat, antelope’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈsprɪŋbɒk/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A small antelope native to southern Africa, capable of running at 80 kilometres/kilometers per hour (50 miles per hour).
# ('''the Springboks''') The name of [[South Africa]]'s national [[rugby union]] team.

